id: pm-f38n
title: "GH-547: SDK exporters and renderers cannot suppress host rendering of handled output"
description: "Track the SDK contract gap where a package-owned exporter or renderer cannot explicitly mark a handled result as already emitted, causing host rendering to corrupt stdout or forcing stderr workarounds."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:extensions","area:output","area:sdk",gh-issue,package-authoring
created_at: "2026-07-13T22:19:34.239Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T18:22:15.910Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T18:08:21.844Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "A typed, documented suppression contract is shared by exporter, renderer, service override, CLI, and MCP dispatch; default behavior remains backward compatible; runtime and package-harness tests cover handled output, suppressed output, JSON/TOON, errors, and telemetry; a packed temp package proves stdout remains uncorrupted"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: high
reporter: codex-root
severity: medium
repro_steps: "Implement a package exporter or renderer that streams or writes its own output, return a normal handled result, and observe the host render the result again because no public suppression sentinel exists."
resolution: Added a typed structural SDK output-suppression protocol and CLI presentation support with optional structured result preservation.
expected_result: "Package commands that own streaming, binary, or pre-rendered stdout can prevent duplicate host rendering."
actual_result: "Every normal handler result was rendered again by the host, corrupting package-owned stdout."
component: "SDK exporter, renderer, and output service contracts"
customer_impact: "Package authors cannot safely implement streaming, binary, or already-rendered export workflows through public SDK primitives."
