comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:19:34.239Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-14: all-status searches for GH-547, suppress host rendering, exporter renderer suppression, and stdout corruption found no existing item. GitHub issue #547 is canonical external evidence; this item is deliberately left open and unclaimed."
  "2026-07-14T18:08:04.049Z",codex-root,"Final evidence: public suppressHostOutput()/isHostOutputSuppressed contracts are exported from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; CLI output ownership unwraps the optional structured result for hooks/telemetry and emits no second payload. Linked pm tests pass; packed package imported the helper and direct stream output was exactly one line. Full coverage is 100/100/100/100."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T18:08:02.499Z",codex-root,"Design rationale: keep the protocol in core output-control, re-export it through sdk/output, and let the CLI presentation layer consume it. This preserves SDK-to-core dependency direction and lets embedded hosts use the same structural guard."
